The paper deals with the quantifier alternation hierarchy in finite variable logics, which is a topic in mathematical logic and theoretical computer science. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of graphs and trees, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of colored graphs and trees may also indicate a connection to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper includes lower bounds on the quantifier depth, which could be of interest to researchers in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
